    <div class="content-container">
        <h1>Press About the Project</h1><br />
        <p>
            The legacy of Krystyna Bednarczyk and her Poets’ and Painters’ Press
            continues to inspire researchers, literary enthusiasts, and artists
            alike. Our project, dedicated to unveiling her contributions to
            Polish and British cultural heritage, has garnered significant
            attention from academic circles and the press. Below, we highlight
            key publications and articles reflecting on Bednarczyk’s remarkable
            impact.
        </p>

        <h3><b>Academic and Media Coverage</b></h3><br />

        <h4><b>Scholarly Articles & Publications</b></h4>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <em
                        >About Krystyna Bednarczyk and Her Poets’ and Painters'
                        Press</em
                    > – Contributions by Caryl Topolski, Magdalena Czajkowska, Aleksandra
                    Dąbrowska, Mieczysława Wazacz, and Anna Frajlich. Featured in
                    <em>Pamiętnik Literacki</em> (Vol. LXVI, December 2023).
                </p>
            </li>
            <li><p> 
                <em
                    >The Bednarczyk Duo and Their Poets’ and Painters’ Press.
                    Hidden Between Covers</em
                > – Justyna Gorzkowicz explores their influence in <em
